9b3defec-0b1d-55c6-b1a7-39121cccba79,tg:rubgr:2804,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"[vouwblad] General Introduction. Bruegel & Van der Goes. Vanbeselaere sees connection between Monforte Altar & Bruegel's N.G. Adoration - not convincing. More correct Fierens-Gevaert. Fierens contention that Patinir Shepherds precursor of Bruegel's peasants. I think the bare December trees with leading into depth and forming a pattern impressed Bruegel in: Return of Herd, Hunters, Gloomy Day, Bird Trap, Census at Bethlehem, Murder of Innocents, Reinhart Adoration, Carneval. Motif of bare tree also in Cockaigne, Triumph of Death i.e. in 13 pictures)[...]",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
